<div class="life col-sm-9">
  <ul>
    <li>26 August 1910: Agnes Gonxha Bojaxhiu later known as Mother  Teresa is born.</li><br>
    <li>1928: Agnes gets a calling from God to help the  poor and helpless.</li><br>
    <li>May 24th 1931: Agnes takes her first vows and changes her  name to Teresa</li><br>
    <li>7 October 1948:  The Missionaries of charity is approved.</li><br>
    <li>1957: Mother Teresa work with the lepers of Calcutta.</li><br>
    <li>1963:  The   Missionaries of Charity Brothers is established.</li><br>
    <li>1965: The Place of Peace for the lepers is opened, otherwise known as Shanti Nagar.
</li><br>
    <li>1979: Mother Teresa is awarded the Nobel Peace  Prize</li><br>
    <li>1985: Mother Teresa receives the Medal of Freedom  from the United States of America.</li><br>
    <li>5 September 1997: Mother Teresa dies from cardiac arrest.</li><br>
    <li>19 October 2003: Mother Teresa is beatified.</li><br>
    <li>4 September 2016: Mother Teresa is canonized</li>
  </ul>
</div>
</div>


